onBind

public void onBind()
Description copied from class: HandlerContainer
Important : Make sure you call your parent class onBind().

This method is called when binding the object. Any event handlers should be initialised here rather than in the constructor. Other costly initialisation should be done here too, in order to speed-up construction.

Handlers registered by calling (HandlerRegistration) will be removed automatically. Any other initialisation that takes place here (or as a side-effect of what is done here) should be taken down in HandlerContainer.unbind().

This method will never be invoked more then once, or if it is, the second time will necessarily be preceded by an invocation of HandlerContainer.unbind().
